steps.text:
Thank you for participating in the Apple Women’s Health Study.

Many things can influence your periods, including different hormones. This survey will ask about symptoms that may be related to your hormone levels. If you are taking medications that may change your body or cycles, like contraceptives or transgender hormone therapy, provide answers about your symptoms before you started these treatments.

steps.text: These questions are about hair growth on your upper lip, chin, breasts, chest, back, abdomen, upper arms, or upper thighs. These questions are not about your eyebrows, under arms, or pubic hair.

learnMoreInstructionStep.text: Acne, which is also called pimples or zits, is a skin condition that occurs when follicles are plugged with oil, bacteria, or dead skin cells.
